Upon completion of the course, students should be able to:
1. Demonstrate a solid understanding of the nature of cultural identity and perceptions of an imagined homeland based on the collective experiences of the Japanese diaspora;
2. Critically analyze the ideas of expansionism, imperialism, and colonialism;
3. Sensitively reflect on the diverse yet individual experiences of Japanese migrants; and
4. Analyze global flows of people, ideas, and products with reference to Japan.
